{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cocaine addiction causes [higher impulsivity](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5817335/), meaning sufferers are more likely to engage in risky behaviour such as gambling. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Without producing all drugs locally inside that border and banning imports, the situation would continue to support foreign criminal activity, including associated acts of violence and social destabilisation in other places where drugs are produced but not legal. {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs inflates its price, which, in turn, promotes distributors to mix it with sometimes dangerous chemical substances to augment its volume.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "In Uruguay, possession of drugs for personal use [is legal](https://www.tni.org/es/node/16660). That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs inflates its price, which, in turn, promotes distributors to mix it with sometimes dangerous chemical substances to augment its volume.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization of drugs will make people aware of their consequences \\(having a prospectus like medicine with known pros and cons - like marijuana for medical usage\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The culture of [overprescription](https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2018/06/opioid-epidemic/563576/) in the medical community has been a significant factor in the opioid crisis. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Alcohol](https://theconversation.com/alcohol-leads-to-more-violence-than-other-drugs-but-youd-never-know-from-the-headlines-72281) is responsible for more violence and harm than any other drug.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are still many other ways in which criminal associations could take advantage of the situation and legally start selling drugs or exploiting the farmers as they do now.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to [Human Right Watch](https://www.hrw.org/news/2013/06/04/americas-decriminalize-personal-use-drugs), subjecting people to disproportionate criminal sanctions for the personal use of drugs "infringes on their autonomy".'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalization of recreational drug use is not necessary for legalization of expanded drug research. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Many Canadian cigarettes are [smuggled back](https://www.publicsafety.gc.ca/cnt/rsrcs/pblctns/archive-stts-cntrbnd-tbcc/index-en.aspx) into Canada.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are more effective policies than legalizing drug use to challenge drug abuse.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's people's own choice whether to be moral or not. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are more effective policies than legalizing drug use to challenge drug abuse.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The Netherlands' comparably liberal [drug policy](https://www.opensocietyfoundations.org/voices/safe-and-effective-drug-policy-look-dutch) has generated positive outcomes."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs being legalized would allow the injured victims \\(or their heirs\\) of fraudulently/irresponsibly cut/marketed drugs to legally and publicly sue the manufacturer/distributor for damages, thereby using market pressures to better assure product/service quality/safety. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Based on countries that have decriminalized drugs like [Portugal](https://borgenproject.org/decriminalization-of-drugs-in-portugal/), drug use has not significantly increased among the poor population, or at all.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Justifying a ban because it provides people with more autonomy is an inherent contradiction. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use is not the same as drug addiction.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Smoking](https://www.cancer.org/cancer/cancer-causes/tobacco-and-cancer/secondhand-smoke.html) puts the drugs into the air, meaning non-consenting people take the drug as well.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When people overdose on illegal drugs medical staff may have a problem knowing what's in the drugs that were ingested. If drugs were legal and regulated, they could save more lives."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Nixon's war on drugs [was started](https://www.cnn.com/2016/03/23/politics/john-ehrlichman-richard-nixon-drug-war-blacks-hippie/index.html) to target blacks and hippies."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legal drugs make it easier for criminals to coerce prostitutes through drug addiction with the state being able to do less to rehabilitate them forcefully. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The black market businesses won't be able to invest in productivity-increasing \\(especially immovable\\) capital, as the threat of being caught discourages such investments. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal cultivation/production of psychoactive compounds on the personal or even community scale could eliminate the international black market for them, making society safer for communities.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A part of the "forbidden fruit" effect is that drugs provide short-term benefit \\(the "high"\\) in exchange for long-term cost \\(negative health impacts\\).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Opiates have a [rich history](https://www.history.com/topics/crime/history-of-heroin-morphine-and-opiates) of recreational use, with the Ancient Sumerians calling it "The Joy Plant".'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This stress would be reduced if the drugs were legal because it would remove the threat of legal danger to any concerned person.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs may lead to children trying and becoming involved with drugs at a younger age.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar compound will always exist.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In India, the mental illness known in the West as [Anomie](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anomie) is cured with the drugs Soma, Amrita, and Ganja plus \\(in a more modern interpretation\\) Peyote and Ayahuasca.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'People may drive under the influence of drugs or make other decisions with public consequences.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even a year after release, former convicts [are 10-18 times more likely](https://sph.unc.edu/sph-news/former-inmates-at-high-risk-for-opioid-overdose-following-prison-release/) to die of an overdose than the average population.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The prohibition forces users, that are otherwise law-abiding citizens, into transactions with more serious law-breakers, opening them up for the possibility to escalate to more serious crimes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The evidence provided in this claim stems largely from importing cheaper cigarettes from the rest of Europe to the UK. The difference in quality is probably minimal. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can give individuals false perceptions of reality, inducing potentially negative behaviour.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Self-medication, for instance with [analgesics](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analgesic), will worsen the disease and delay proper treatment. So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If established companies behave inappropriately with regards to the selling of drugs, people would be able to report this without fear of facing consequences for trying to buy drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cannabis-derived approved drugs containing \\(half-synthetic\\) THC or CBD [can be researched](https://accpjournals.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1002/phar.1187) as an alternative to cannabis.'}
